What's the actual auto-approve target rate by Year 1 / Year 2 / Year 3? This determines whether the FTE business case is conservative or aggressive.
What's the policy lifecycle? When a new fund/client onboards, who creates the new pricing policy YAML? How long until it's eligible for auto-approval? This is the operational onboarding question.
What's the policy for "policies the agent has never seen"? Default to 100% HITL until N successful approvals? Or block the policy entirely until reviewed?
Are there any "always HITL" policies? Regulatory or client-mandated — some funds may require human review for every exception regardless of confidence. Need to know upfront.

Is Temporal available in BNP infrastructure? If not, what durable workflow option exists?
What's the integration model with AMANDA — direct DB read, REST API, Kafka topic? Determines the intake design.
Who owns rule authoring day-to-day — ops, ADM, or a hybrid? Determines the UI design.
What's the existing audit/evidence storage standard at BNP? Reuse if possible; don't reinvent.
How does this integrate with AEX (the new Amanda model)? Critical — if AEX is rewriting Amanda anyway, this work should be designed to ride on AEX, not be retrofit later.
Is there a "Phase 0" budget for the Rule Repository product itself, separate from the AI work? If yes, that's the right place to start funding.
